Title : Prospect Point (British Columbia)
Text : '''Prospect Point''' is a point at the northern tip of [[Stanley Park]] in [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]], [[Canada]], located on the south side of the First Narrows of [[Burrard Inlet]].  The point, which as its name suggests, is a viewpoint, landmark and tourist attraction in Stanley Park and has a restaurant and other facilities, is just west of the [[Lions Gate Bridge]].<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/21275.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Prospect Point"]</ref>
[[Image:Prospect Point Viewpoint.jpg|thumb|Looking northeast from Prospect Point Viewpoint]]
The location of the point is known in the [[Skwxwu7mesh language|Skwxwu7mesh (Squamish) language]] as ''Chay-thoos'', meaning "high bank".<ref>{{cite web| title =Early Vancouver Volume 2: Narrative of Pioneers of Vancouver, BC Collected During 1932| publisher =City of Vancouver| url =https://archive.org/stream/EarlyVancouverVolume2/MatthewsEarlyVancouverVol2_FullVersionPDF-A_djvu.txt| accessdate = 2013-08-16}}</ref>  According to [[Pauline Johnson]]'s account in ''Legends of Vancouver'', in Skwxwu7mesh tradition inside the cliffs that mark the point from the water lived a spirit-being with the power to bring storms and rain.<ref>''Legends of Vancouver'', Pauline Johnson</ref>

